About Salvador Villalon
My name is Salvador Villalon and I am a Junior at the
University of California, Irvine studying Computer Science.
My love for technology began when I designed and created
my first website for the Administrative Intern Program. After finishing
this project, I reliaze how important technology is. This project
may have been small, but it was doing two important things
that a Software Engineer always does. This website was introducing
students to a program that can enhance their college and professional careers.
At the same time, it was helping increase the brand and awareness of
the Administrative Intern Program.
I realize that this is exactly what a Software Engineer does. They
create the tools that organizations and people need to move forward.
Thanks to this project, it guide me on my goal of becoming a Software Engineer.
